EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use due back on 11/10/2004.
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to authorizing the department of transportation to extend the expiration date of any franchise to operate and maintain bus stop shelters.
EventItemMatterName: Authorizing the DOT to extend the expiration date of any franchise to operate and maintain bus shelters.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs due back on 11/10/2004.
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the license application requirements for general and food street vendors and to repeal paragraph 7 of subdivision b of section 17-309 and paragraph 6 of subdivision b of section 20-455 of the administrative code of the city of New York.
EventItemMatterName: License application requirements for general and food street vendors.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare due back on 11/10/2004.

EventItemMatterName: Establishing a child welfare parent advocate advisory program and a child welfare parent advocate advisory board.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology in Government due back on 11/10/2004.
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon all relevant City agencies to use their funding and regulatory power to support and encourage the provision of affordable high-speed Internet service and computer purchases for the benefit of residents of affordable housing.
EventItemMatterName: Support and encourage the provision of affordable high-speed Internet service and computer purchases for the benefit of residents of affordable housing.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education due back on 11/10/2004.

EventItemMatterName: Address the MTA’s projected budget deficit in 2005.

EventItemMatterName: Creating vessel regulation zones within the Harlem River.
